---
title: Steak and Brussels Sprout Stir-Fry with Carrot, Ginger, and Jasmine Rice
description: Brussels sprouts and stir-fry may sound like an unlikely pair, but trust us, it works. The addition of this cruciferous veggie adds a seasonal flair to the dish—not to mention a hefty dose of iron and Vitamins A and C. Feel free to add as much or as little jalapeño as you like. After all, you’re the chef!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/steak-and-brussel-sprout-stir-fr-4205398a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/steak-and-brussel-sprout-stir-fr-ebbee8a8.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 540 kcal
  fat: 9 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 47 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 889 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/steak-and-brussels-sprout-stir-fry-57f66700c726287789402ef2
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: Asian
time required: 30 minutes
---

Bring @water{1%cup}(salted) to a boil in a #medium pot{}. Once boiling, add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Cover and reduce heat to low. Simmer until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove from heat until meal is ready.

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and quarter @brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Peel and cut @carrots{1}(peeled and cut on a diagonal into thin slices). Thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping whites and greens separate. Thinly slice @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Halve @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season @beef sirloin tips{12%ounce} on all sides with @salt{some} and @pepper{some}. Sear until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside.

Add Brussels sprouts, carrots, and as much jalapeño as you like to same pan. Toss until veggies are just barely tender, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Finish the stir-fry: Add scallion whites and ginger. Toss until veggies are softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Add @soy sauce{1%ounce}, steak, and a squeeze of lemon. Toss until steak is cooked to desired doneness, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Serve: Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Serve stir-fry on a bed of rice, top with scallion greens, and enjoy!

> Brussels sprouts and stir-fry may sound like an unlikely pair, but trust us, it works. The addition of this cruciferous veggie adds a seasonal flair to the dish—not to mention a hefty dose of iron and Vitamins A and C. Feel free to add as much or as little jalapeño as you like. After all, you're the chef!